#originalTopic=Debate:_DC_handgun_ban
The DC handgun ban did decrease crime immediately after passing. The DC handgun ban did decrease crime and murder rates directly after the ban was passed. According to CBS news, "Homicides in the district did ebb over the next few years, largely following a national trend. In 1977, the U.S. Conference of Mayors reported robberies, assaults and homicides using handguns had fallen sharply in D.C. and concluded the ban was working. However, the results were challenged even by the city's police department, which said police tactics had contributed to the drop."[5]
